5
00:00:19,417 --> 00:00:22,458
[NARRATOR] an average
person's many times over.

6
00:00:22,542 --> 00:00:23,833
[NARRATOR] We were shoved to

7
00:00:23,917 --> 00:00:26,417
[NARRATOR] the brink of
extinction almost overnight.

8
00:00:31,167 --> 00:00:35,292
[NARRATOR] The survivors erected
Walls Maria, Rose, and Sina;

9
00:00:35,375 --> 00:00:37,708
[NARRATOR] withdrawing behind
them in frightened huddles for

10
00:00:37,792 --> 00:00:41,500
[NARRATOR] what was to be
a century of uneasy peace.

11
00:00:41,583 --> 00:00:42,875
[NARRATOR] And then...

12
00:02:32,083 --> 00:02:34,042
Caw!

13
00:02:34,125 --> 00:02:38,333
"'Til then a man apart
from God. O wretched was I.

14
00:02:38,417 --> 00:02:41,708
And driven e'en as
a plough by avarice."

15
00:02:42,250 --> 00:02:45,958
[PREACHER] "Now, thou behold'st,
am I here punished for it.

16
00:02:46,042 --> 00:02:49,083
[PREACHER] Punished
by the justice of God."

17
00:02:49,167 --> 00:02:52,458
[PREACHER] "Where covetousness
leads, thou sees't bourn.

18
00:02:52,542 --> 00:02:55,542
[PREACHER] Upon the penance
of these writhing souls,

19
00:02:55,625 --> 00:02:59,375
[PREACHER] the Mountain
holds no greater pain!"

20
00:02:59,458 --> 00:03:02,583
[PREACHER] "As greed has drowned
our love for every good,

21
00:03:02,667 --> 00:03:05,917
[PREACHER] every right,
so justice here doth chain."

22
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:09,125
[panting]

23
00:03:18,667 --> 00:03:22,708
[screaming] Please! No!

24
00:03:22,792 --> 00:03:26,750
[PREACHER] "Tethered, captive,
are; merged with the clay.

25
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:30,500
[PREACHER] And thus to remain
so long as it pleases The Lord:

26
00:03:30,583 --> 00:03:33,875
[PREACHER] fraught, fixed,
earthen in heart and limb."

27
00:03:33,958 --> 00:03:38,292
"What else may heav'nly grace
do for sins as ours?" Huh?

28
00:03:41,125 --> 00:03:44,000
[PREACHER] "For we lifted not
our eye to heights bequeathed,

29
00:03:44,083 --> 00:03:45,875
[PREACHER] and like the plou--"

30
00:03:49,333 --> 00:03:58,000
[heavy breathing]

31
00:03:58,083 --> 00:03:59,208
[punch]

32
00:03:59,292 --> 00:04:00,625
[HANNES] Damn it! Stop!

33
00:04:00,708 --> 00:04:03,792
[EREN] You son of a bitch!
We could've saved her!

34
00:04:03,875 --> 00:04:07,625
We almost had her out!
Why did you come? Why?

35
00:04:07,708 --> 00:04:09,375
[HANNES] I told you to stop!

36
00:04:10,875 --> 00:04:12,292
Eren!

37
00:04:17,292 --> 00:04:18,500
[HANNES] Look...

38
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:22,917
[HANNES] There's nothing
you could've done for her,

39
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:26,917
[HANNES] you understand?
You're a kid; you're weak.

40
00:04:29,792 --> 00:04:33,167
[HANNES] I'm worse.
When push came to shove,

41
00:04:33,250 --> 00:04:36,125
I was too frightened
to hold my ground.

42
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:40,042
Your mother died because
I'm a damn coward!

43
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:52,083
[HANNES] I'm sorry.

44
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:06,292
It's the same
thing all over again.

45
00:05:14,875 --> 00:05:20,208
[screaming]

46
00:05:20,292 --> 00:05:23,042
Hurry up! Keep your
eye on the Gate!

47
00:05:23,125 --> 00:05:25,333
[HUGO] Drop everything,
find the ferry nearest you

48
00:05:25,417 --> 00:05:28,208
[HUGO] and climb aboard
for all you're worth! Move it!

49
00:05:28,292 --> 00:05:31,000
[HUGO] These things aren't
gonna give you a head start!

50
00:05:44,208 --> 00:05:47,417
[NARRATOR] So-called Outlier
Districts like Shiganshina

51
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:50,667
[NARRATOR]  jut out like thorns
at vital spots along Wall Maria.

52
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:53,708
[NARRATOR] Their basic
function is to streamline

53
00:05:53,792 --> 00:05:55,625
[NARRATOR] troop dispersal
and keep security costs down by

54
00:05:55,708 --> 00:05:58,167
[NARRATOR] drawing Titans
into specific areas.

55
00:05:58,250 --> 00:05:59,958
[NARRATOR] The calculated
design flaw in all

56
00:06:00,042 --> 00:06:02,292
[NARRATOR] Outlier Districts
is that they have only

57
00:06:02,375 --> 00:06:04,042
[NARRATOR] a single gate
through which its citizens

58
00:06:04,125 --> 00:06:05,833
[NARRATOR] are able
to retreat deeper inward

59
00:06:05,917 --> 00:06:07,583
[NARRATOR] should
the need arise.

60
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:11,417
No personal belongings!
We need to make

61
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:13,833
as much room as possible!

62
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:20,500
Armin. You best have a seat.

63
00:06:20,583 --> 00:06:23,833
I will. Just keeping
an eye out for my friends.

64
00:06:24,792 --> 00:06:26,167
There they are!

65
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:30,083
[ARMIN] Eren.

66
00:06:31,875 --> 00:06:34,083
I wouldn't try
to call out just now.

67
00:06:34,167 --> 00:06:38,417
Give 'em their space. God only
knows what they've just seen.

68
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:41,875
[panicking]

69
00:06:41,958 --> 00:06:44,208
Stop dragging your
feet! Snap out of it!

70
00:06:44,292 --> 00:06:46,333
I need those canons loaded!

71
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:56,458
C'mon! They're
headed right for us!

72
00:06:56,542 --> 00:07:04,167
[screaming]

73
00:07:04,250 --> 00:07:06,708
[panting]

74
00:07:11,375 --> 00:07:14,500
[MALE CITIZEN] This isn't
real. This is a nightmare.

75
00:07:14,583 --> 00:07:17,833
[FEMALE CITIZEN] God help us.
God help us. God help us.

76
00:07:17,917 --> 00:07:19,083
[panic and shouting]

77
00:07:19,167 --> 00:07:20,625
[MALE CITIZEN]
Hey! What are you doing?

78
00:07:21,375 --> 00:07:23,292
[MALE CITIZEN] What are the
rest of us supposed to do?

79
00:07:23,375 --> 00:07:24,625
[ELITE] I'm sorry,
it's at full capacity!

80
00:07:24,708 --> 00:07:26,208
[FEMALE CITIZEN]
You can't do this! Please!

81
00:07:26,292 --> 00:07:28,208
[FEMALE CITIZEN] At least
let our children on board!

82
00:07:28,292 --> 00:07:31,792
Look, there's nothing
we can do! Push off, now!

83
00:07:35,417 --> 00:07:36,458
[FEMALE CITIZEN]
Don't leave us!

84
00:07:36,542 --> 00:07:38,292
[MALE CITIZEN]
There's still room!

85
00:07:38,625 --> 00:07:41,917
[panic]

86
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:53,500
