87
00:07:53,583 --> 00:07:55,875
What are you aiming at? Have
you got rocks in your head?

88
00:07:55,958 --> 00:07:58,625
Sir. With respect, they're
old as sin and not designed

89
00:07:58,708 --> 00:08:00,333
for accuracy to begin with!

90
00:08:00,417 --> 00:08:02,625
[HUGO] You gonna give me
attitude or you gonna reload?

91
00:08:02,708 --> 00:08:04,542
[HUGO] Stop whining
and do your job!

92
00:08:04,625 --> 00:08:06,375
[ELITE] What's the point?

93
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:13,875
No. The Inner Gate.

94
00:08:13,958 --> 00:08:15,667
I'm not getting left behind.

95
00:08:15,750 --> 00:08:16,542
[ELITE] Retreat or die!

96
00:08:16,625 --> 00:08:17,750
Hey!

97
00:08:19,375 --> 00:08:21,500
[HANNES] Wait! Are you out of
your mind? Don't shut it yet!

98
00:08:21,583 --> 00:08:24,292
[HANNES] We've still got people
out there! Give 'em a chance!

99
00:08:24,375 --> 00:08:26,542
We can't let the Titans
get through the Inner Gate.

100
00:08:26,625 --> 00:08:28,458
If that happens, the handful
of lives left out there'll be

101
00:08:28,542 --> 00:08:31,083
the least of our problems! There
aren't enough resources for

102
00:08:31,167 --> 00:08:32,750
the whole human
race to retreat behind

103
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:33,833
the next wall if
they break through!

104
00:08:33,917 --> 00:08:35,833
Listen to yourself!
We're soldiers;

105
00:08:35,917 --> 00:08:38,208
we don't get to decide
who lives or dies!

106
00:08:38,292 --> 00:08:39,583
What are you waiting for?

107
00:08:39,667 --> 00:08:42,250
The Titans are
closing the gap!

108
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:44,250
That does it, bring 'er down!

109
00:08:46,167 --> 00:08:47,375
No!

110
00:08:49,083 --> 00:08:51,417
Let go of me!

111
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:52,917
[gasp]

112
00:08:55,125 --> 00:08:56,542
[gasp]

113
00:08:59,708 --> 00:09:09,667
♪

114
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:19,667
♪

115
00:09:19,750 --> 00:09:28,917
♪

116
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,708
[HUGO] What the hell?

117
00:09:31,792 --> 00:09:33,125
[HUGO] Oh no.

118
00:09:33,875 --> 00:09:35,250
Fire!

119
00:09:42,458 --> 00:09:43,500
What?

120
00:09:43,583 --> 00:09:45,000
Impossible!

121
00:09:47,250 --> 00:09:49,667
We've gotta get
the hell out of here!

122
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:53,792
Retreat! Retreat!

123
00:09:53,875 --> 00:09:57,458
Shut the gate, now!
We're being charged!

124
00:09:57,542 --> 00:10:00,083
[HUGO] Go, go, go!

125
00:10:00,167 --> 00:10:10,167
♪

126
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:20,167
♪

127
00:10:20,250 --> 00:10:31,542
♪

128
00:10:31,625 --> 00:10:34,750
[shaky breathing]

129
00:10:34,833 --> 00:10:37,333
[HANNES] Oh, God.

130
00:11:05,292 --> 00:11:07,375
[NARRATOR] Bad news
travels fast.

131
00:11:07,458 --> 00:11:09,208
[NARRATOR] Hours
after Shiganshina fell,

132
00:11:09,292 --> 00:11:12,000
[NARRATOR] every man, woman,
and child within the Interior

133
00:11:12,083 --> 00:11:14,792
[NARRATOR] knew the unthinkable
had come to pass.

134
00:11:14,875 --> 00:11:17,417
[NARRATOR] Terror
spread like wildfire.

135
00:11:17,500 --> 00:11:19,042
[LORD] What do you think we're
meant to make of these reports

136
00:11:19,125 --> 00:11:21,458
[LORD] of Shiganshina
falling to the Titans?

137
00:11:21,542 --> 00:11:24,083
Are they verified?
That outcropping has held

138
00:11:24,167 --> 00:11:26,583
for a century;
it makes no sense.

139
00:11:26,667 --> 00:11:29,458
Whether or not they're verified.
The refugees are certainly

140
00:11:29,542 --> 00:11:31,500
flooding in like plague rats.

141
00:11:31,583 --> 00:11:32,667
There've been at least

142
00:11:32,750 --> 00:11:34,500
five-hundred accounted
for in the boats.

143
00:11:34,583 --> 00:11:38,792
The question is how prepared are
we if Shiganshina is in ruins?

144
00:11:38,875 --> 00:11:41,833
Come now. Surely Wall Maria
is enough on its own to

145
00:11:41,917 --> 00:11:44,417
hold the Titans at
bay, don't you think?

146
00:11:46,917 --> 00:11:50,667
Damn it all. Any way it's sliced
the situation is untenable.

147
00:11:50,750 --> 00:11:53,750
Our hands are tied.
I say we make appeals

148
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:55,667
to the Central
Government for help.

149
00:11:56,042 --> 00:11:57,250
[ELITE] Excuse me, my lords!

150
00:11:57,333 --> 00:11:59,125
You'll really
want to hear this!

151
00:11:59,208 --> 00:12:01,083
Wall Maria's been
broken through.

152
00:12:01,167 --> 00:12:03,458
The Titans are-- They're in!

153
00:12:11,958 --> 00:12:13,750
This is the end.

154
00:12:15,042 --> 00:12:18,333
[COMMONER] That's it.
We're all dead.

155
00:12:18,417 --> 00:12:20,875
We're dead and standing
at the gate of Hell.

156
00:12:22,167 --> 00:12:23,958
[EREN] It's gone.

157
00:12:24,583 --> 00:12:29,875
Our house. It's
all gone. Forever.

158
00:12:32,708 --> 00:12:34,500
[EREN] Forever.

159
00:12:35,708 --> 00:12:37,708
[EREN] Why was I
always such a brat?

160
00:12:37,792 --> 00:12:39,792
[EREN] Why did I
always fight her?

161
00:12:39,875 --> 00:12:43,250
[EREN] I never said,
"I love you."

162
00:12:43,333 --> 00:12:45,750
[EREN] Now I'll never get to.

163
00:12:47,750 --> 00:12:49,500
[EREN] Never!

164
00:12:50,250 --> 00:12:53,583
There's nothing you could've
done for her, you understand?

165
00:12:55,375 --> 00:12:59,458
Because I'm a kid.
Because I'm weak.

166
00:12:59,542 --> 00:13:03,292
Because every last one
of us is a damn coward!

167
00:13:07,167 --> 00:13:10,125
[fighting tears]

168
00:13:17,458 --> 00:13:20,167
[EREN] No. This is over.

169
00:13:20,250 --> 00:13:21,458
What're you--?

170
00:13:21,542 --> 00:13:23,375
[ARMIN] What's wrong?
You see something?

171
00:13:24,292 --> 00:13:25,583
[ARMIN] Eren.

172
00:13:26,625 --> 00:13:28,875
I'm going to
put a stop to this!

173
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,875
I'll kill them all.

174
00:13:31,958 --> 00:13:34,792
Every last one.

175
00:13:35,958 --> 00:13:37,500
Eren.

176
00:13:43,292 --> 00:13:45,583
[NARRATOR] In terrified haste,
The Central Government

177
00:13:45,667 --> 00:13:48,292
[NARRATOR] declared the
Outlier Districts a lost cause

178
00:13:48,375 --> 00:13:50,375
[NARRATOR] and decreed
all mankind retreat

179
00:13:50,458 --> 00:13:53,250
[NARRATOR] behind Wall Rose.
Estimates held that nearly

180
00:13:53,333 --> 00:13:55,292
[NARRATOR] ten-thousand
lives were lost

181
00:13:55,375 --> 00:13:57,292
[NARRATOR] to the
Titan offensive.

182
00:13:58,833 --> 00:14:05,375
Eren. Carla. Mikasa.
Please be alive!

183
00:14:07,917 --> 00:14:13,083
[GRISHA] Eren! Stay
with me, boy! Wake up!

184
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:16,708
[EREN] Stop it!
Please, you're scaring me!

185
00:14:17,583 --> 00:14:19,500
[EREN] I don't understand
what you're trying to do!

186
00:14:19,583 --> 00:14:21,458
[GRISHA] You don't have to!
Just give me your arm!

187
00:14:21,542 --> 00:14:23,917
[EREN] No! You're insane!

188
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:26,000
[EREN] Mom's death pushed
you off the deep end!

189
00:14:26,083 --> 00:14:27,375
[GRISHA] Shut up!

190
00:14:27,458 --> 00:14:29,583
[EREN] Get off! Let me go!

191
00:14:29,667 --> 00:14:31,833
Damn you, this
is the only way!

192
00:14:31,917 --> 00:14:33,875
[EREN] You're not
making any sense!

193
00:14:34,458 --> 00:14:36,042
[GRISHA] You cannot
forget the key!

194
00:14:36,125 --> 00:14:38,833
[GRISHA] Whatever you
do, you must reach it!

195
00:14:38,917 --> 00:14:40,792
[GRISHA] It's the
way to the Truth!

196
00:14:40,875 --> 00:14:42,625
[GRISHA] One day
you'll understand!

197
00:14:42,708 --> 00:14:51,583
[bells ringing]

198
00:14:51,667 --> 00:14:55,667
Hey. It's okay.
You were just dreaming.

199
00:14:55,750 --> 00:15:00,042
Dad was-- It felt so real.

200
00:15:00,125 --> 00:15:02,375
Nightmare. Shake it off.

201
00:15:03,417 --> 00:15:05,375
Yeah.

202
00:15:08,917 --> 00:15:10,208
[MIKASA] Come on.

203
00:15:10,292 --> 00:15:13,417
They're handing out food
rations near the warehouse.

204
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:19,583
[MIKASA] I think this
used to be where they

205
00:15:19,667 --> 00:15:21,625
[MIKASA] stored
all the dry goods.

206
00:15:21,708 --> 00:15:24,292
[MIKASA] Now it's where
they corral the refugees.

207
00:15:26,458 --> 00:15:27,917
[gasp]

208
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:36,042
[chattering]

209
00:15:36,125 --> 00:15:37,583
[COMMONER] I don't
think so, friend!

210
00:15:37,667 --> 00:15:39,000
[ANOTHER COMMONER]
Give me a break!

211
00:15:39,083 --> 00:15:41,417
All I've had for two
days is a moldy bit of crust!

212
00:15:41,958 --> 00:15:45,000
Not exactly a
dignified existence.

213
00:15:45,625 --> 00:15:47,125
[ARMIN] Hey guys!

214
00:15:48,667 --> 00:15:50,000
[EREN] Armin.

215
00:15:51,458 --> 00:15:54,792
Glad I caught you. Here.
Grandpa scrounged a little extra

216
00:15:54,875 --> 00:15:57,125
by telling the
powers-that-be he had kids.

217
00:15:57,208 --> 00:15:58,625
That was nice of him.

218
00:16:02,542 --> 00:16:03,875
Tch!

219
00:16:05,292 --> 00:16:06,458
What's his deal?

220
00:16:06,542 --> 00:16:09,208
Just ignore it.
There's a shortage.

221
00:16:09,292 --> 00:16:11,292
Poor man's probably hungry.

222
00:16:11,375 --> 00:16:13,708
By the way,
I'd make that last.

223
00:16:13,792 --> 00:16:15,500
[ARMIN] They were
already dealing with famine

224
00:16:15,583 --> 00:16:17,083
[ARMIN] before we
got here, so it's

225
00:16:17,167 --> 00:16:19,875
[ARMIN] an ugly situation.
That, and this far in

226
00:16:19,958 --> 00:16:21,542
[ARMIN] there's a
greater disparity between

227
00:16:21,625 --> 00:16:23,458
[ARMIN] the haves
and the have-nots.

228
00:16:23,542 --> 00:16:24,583
Nothin' more gratifyin' than

229
00:16:24,667 --> 00:16:26,833
seein' your rations
go to animals.

230
00:16:27,917 --> 00:16:30,208
Guess we gotta beef
up the herd, though.

231
00:16:30,292 --> 00:16:33,375
Eat up, the Titans like a
little meat on their bones!

232
00:16:36,875 --> 00:16:38,375
Eren, wait!

233
00:16:38,458 --> 00:16:39,667
Oughta keep you in cages.

234
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:41,958
Shove you out to the
frontlines as a buffer.

235
00:16:42,042 --> 00:16:46,333
Oww! Damn it! You picked
the wrong man, asshole!

236
00:16:48,750 --> 00:16:51,250
Spineless cowards! All of you!

237
00:16:51,333 --> 00:16:53,875
You don't-- You don't
know what it's like!

238
00:16:53,958 --> 00:16:55,042
Huh?

239
00:16:55,125 --> 00:16:58,542
You seen one? You
seen what they can do?

240
00:17:00,083 --> 00:17:01,333
You little piece o'--

241
00:17:01,417 --> 00:17:04,667
He's sorry! He didn't
mean it; he's just hungry.

