00:17:04,750 --> 00:17:08,708
We all get that way; speak our
minds out of turn sometimes?

243
00:17:08,792 --> 00:17:11,792
Forgive him. I beg you.

244
00:17:14,625 --> 00:17:16,708
Yeah, well. Keep in
mind who's givin' up

245
00:17:16,792 --> 00:17:18,708
their share so you can eat.

246
00:17:18,792 --> 00:17:21,708
In case you hadn't
noticed, we're all hungry.

247
00:17:21,792 --> 00:17:24,750
[ELITE] Tell your buddy a little
gratitude goes a long way.

248
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:26,333
Sure!

249
00:17:26,417 --> 00:17:31,083
Bastard. I'm not about to
show gratitude to a coward!

250
00:17:32,292 --> 00:17:35,542
[EREN] I can't do this.
I'm going back to Wall Maria.

251
00:17:35,625 --> 00:17:38,667
[EREN] The Titans have to pay
for what they've done to us.

252
00:17:38,750 --> 00:17:42,000
Hey, now. You're not serious;
that's your stomach talking.

253
00:17:42,083 --> 00:17:43,375
No, it's not!

254
00:17:43,458 --> 00:17:45,917
Wake up! The guys standing
between us and them

255
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,833
are just a bunch of talk!

256
00:17:48,792 --> 00:17:51,542
To hell with all of 'em!
Here. I'm going back!

257
00:17:52,458 --> 00:17:54,583
Yeah? What're you
tying to do, starve?

258
00:17:54,667 --> 00:17:56,583
When are you gonna
get sick of their charity?

259
00:17:56,667 --> 00:17:58,042
Too much is handed to us!

260
00:17:58,125 --> 00:17:59,958
We have to stand
on our own two feet!

261
00:18:00,042 --> 00:18:02,167
To do what? Get
killed by a Titan?

262
00:18:02,250 --> 00:18:03,625
I know I used
to think our future

263
00:18:03,708 --> 00:18:06,417
was beyond the walls. But
it's like you told that man.

264
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:08,250
I'd never seen what
they could do to us!

265
00:18:08,333 --> 00:18:10,583
So that's it? This
is just the way life is?

266
00:18:10,667 --> 00:18:12,208
Run away and take
what we're given?

267
00:18:12,292 --> 00:18:14,583
Look at us! What
choice do we have here?

268
00:18:14,667 --> 00:18:17,417
We can damn-well leave!
If you wanna scrape by on

269
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:19,375
the charity of cowards,
that's your thing,

270
00:18:19,458 --> 00:18:21,542
but I'm not a parasite!

271
00:18:25,375 --> 00:18:27,125
[ARMIN] Mikasa.

272
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:36,958
[MIKASA] Have you looked
in the mirror lately?

273
00:18:37,042 --> 00:18:39,208
[MIKASA] All of
us are parasites.

274
00:18:39,292 --> 00:18:41,667
[MIKASA] We couldn't run from
certain death without help.

275
00:18:41,750 --> 00:18:43,167
[MIKASA] Tell me differently.

276
00:18:43,250 --> 00:18:45,917
[MIKASA] Don't take your
shortcomings out on him.

277
00:18:46,667 --> 00:18:50,125
[MIKASA] For god's sake, we
can't even find food on our own.

278
00:18:50,208 --> 00:18:52,750
[MIKASA] We're parasites.
We're cowards.

279
00:18:52,833 --> 00:18:55,792
[MIKASA] Titans are at the
top of the food chain. Period.

280
00:18:57,250 --> 00:18:59,792
Pride be damned; we
do what we must to live.

281
00:18:59,875 --> 00:19:02,375
Your mom didn't
ask us to be brave.

282
00:19:08,292 --> 00:19:09,917
Mikasa!

283
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:12,625
Eat it. She asked
us to stay alive.

284
00:19:12,708 --> 00:19:14,833
I'm not about to let her down.

285
00:19:17,042 --> 00:19:21,375
[crying]

286
00:19:21,458 --> 00:19:26,500
♪

287
00:19:26,583 --> 00:19:29,542
[NARRATOR] A few days later,
throngs of starved refugees

288
00:19:29,625 --> 00:19:31,333
[NARRATOR] were put to
plough in the wastelands

289
00:19:31,417 --> 00:19:34,000
[NARRATOR] as a last-ditch
effort to raise food.

290
00:19:36,458 --> 00:19:39,833
[NARRATOR] But the cold,
hard ground yielded nothing.

291
00:19:39,917 --> 00:19:43,542
[NARRATOR] And the following
year, 846, the remaining

292
00:19:43,625 --> 00:19:45,583
[NARRATOR] refugees old enough
to serve in the military

293
00:19:45,667 --> 00:19:48,500
[NARRATOR] were tasked
with reclaiming Wall Maria.

294
00:19:56,500 --> 00:19:59,625
[NARRATOR] Of the 250,000 sent,

295
00:19:59,708 --> 00:20:03,167
[NARRATOR] nearly twenty percent
of the surviving population,

296
00:20:03,250 --> 00:20:06,208
[NARRATOR] not even
two hundred made it back.

297
00:20:07,583 --> 00:20:10,208
[NARRATOR] While it did nothing
to drive back the Titans,

298
00:20:10,292 --> 00:20:12,625
[NARRATOR] their sacrifice
did at least lessen the effects

299
00:20:12,708 --> 00:20:15,750
[NARRATOR] of famine
within the Interior.

300
00:20:21,958 --> 00:20:27,500
[crying]

301
00:20:27,583 --> 00:20:30,333
[EREN] We have to
find a way to stop them.

302
00:20:30,417 --> 00:20:33,917
[EREN] Our lives will never
be our own until we do.

303
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:37,042
[EREN] This world
will never feel like home.

304
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:44,042
That's it. Next year I'll
be applying to join the Cadets.

305
00:20:46,583 --> 00:20:49,333
To become strong
enough to fight back.

306
00:20:52,792 --> 00:20:54,083
I'm with you.

307
00:20:54,167 --> 00:20:55,292
You don't have to--

308
00:20:55,375 --> 00:20:56,792
I do.

309
00:20:57,958 --> 00:20:59,458
[MIKASA] So do I.

310
00:20:59,542 --> 00:21:02,375
Damn it! I'm not
trying to drag you in.

311
00:21:02,458 --> 00:21:05,125
Look, there's no point
in following me to my death!

312
00:21:05,208 --> 00:21:09,708
Yeah. And if I can help it,
then it won't be your death.

313
00:21:13,917 --> 00:21:16,958
All right. Together then.

314
00:21:23,792 --> 00:21:25,792
[KEITH] Straighten
those spines, piss-ants!

315
00:21:25,875 --> 00:21:29,250
[KEITH] The 104th Cadet
Corps Boot Camp starts now!

316
00:21:29,333 --> 00:21:32,667
Allow me to introduce myself:
I'm Commandant Keith Sadies;

317
00:21:32,750 --> 00:21:34,458
And you will grow to hate me.

318
00:21:34,542 --> 00:21:37,333
Training is gonna be a
white-knuckle ride through Hell.

319
00:21:37,417 --> 00:21:40,000
If I've done my job, you'll
be waking up in a cold sweat

320
00:21:40,083 --> 00:21:42,042
[KEITH] from memories
of this place every night

321
00:21:42,125 --> 00:21:44,208
[KEITH] for the rest
of your miserable lives.

322
00:21:44,292 --> 00:21:47,042
[KEITH] Right now,
you're nothing. Livestock.

323
00:21:47,125 --> 00:21:49,917
[KEITH] But over the next
three, soul-crushing years,

324
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:52,833
[KEITH] you'll learn to
take down your own Goliath.

325
00:21:52,917 --> 00:21:55,250
[KEITH] Remember this moment
when you come face to face

326
00:21:55,333 --> 00:21:58,958
[KEIHT] with him, 'cause
here's where you ask yourself:

327
00:21:59,042 --> 00:22:02,083
[KEITH] Am I a fighter,
or am I feed?

328
00:22:02,167 --> 00:22:04,333
[KEITH] Am I gonna be ground
up to pulpy human grist

329
00:22:04,417 --> 00:22:06,583
'tween boulder-sized incisors.

330
00:22:06,667 --> 00:22:09,500
[KEITH] Or am I gonna
be the one to bite?

331
00:22:09,583 --> 00:22:14,333
Oh, I'm a fighter, alright.
And before I'm done with 'em,

332
00:22:14,417 --> 00:22:17,625
the Titans will
grow to hate me.

333
00:23:57,625 --> 00:23:59,208
[NARRATOR] It isn't easy.

334
00:23:59,292 --> 00:24:02,292
[NARRATOR] Hard truth:
Passion's no guarantee you'll

335
00:24:02,375 --> 00:24:05,292
[NARRATOR] stick the landing.
Unless you can transmute it

336
00:24:05,375 --> 00:24:07,917
[NARRATOR] into skill. When
you're floored by fundamentals

337
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:10,917
[NARRATOR] all the heart in
the world means nothing.
